## Read First
Always read AGENTS.md before starting any task.
It contains current build status, migration number,
and prevents rebuilding things that already exist.

# Hi Tech Software — Cursor Rules

## Project
Service Management System for Hi Tech Engineering, Kottayam Kerala.
Client: Hi Tech Engineering
Developer: Supportta Solutions Private Limited
Phone: +91 85903 77418
Stack: Next.js 16.1.6 App Router, Supabase, TypeScript,
TailwindCSS 4, TanStack Query, Zustand, React Hook Form, Zod,
React 19.2.3, Turbopack enabled by default, React Compiler enabled.
Flutter apps: hitech_admin and hitech_technician.
Monorepo: npm workspaces + Turborepo
Node: >= 22

## Folder Structure
- Web app: /web
- Admin Flutter: /hitech_admin
- Technician Flutter: /hitech_technician
- Database migrations: /supabase/migrations
- Docs: /doc
- Work log: /doc/WORK_LOG.md
- Agent prompts: /.cursor/prompts

## Architecture — NEVER VIOLATE THIS
UI (app/) → Hook (hooks/) → Service (modules/) → Repository (repositories/) → Supabase

- Never call Supabase directly from UI components
- Never call Supabase directly from hooks
- Never put business logic in repositories
- Never put UI logic in services
- All forms use React Hook Form + Zod validation
- All server state uses TanStack Query
- Always use existing ProtectedComponent for role-based UI
- Pages must stay under 150 lines — extract sections into components
- Every new module follows this file structure:
  modules/[name]/[name].types.ts
  modules/[name]/[name].constants.ts
  modules/[name]/[name].validation.ts
  modules/[name]/[name].service.ts
  repositories/[name].repository.ts
  hooks/[name]/use[Name].ts
  components/[name]/
  app/dashboard/[name]/page.tsx

## Roles
- super_admin — full access to everything
- office_staff — subjects, customers, billing, team view
- stock_manager — inventory, stock, digital bag only
- technician — own jobs only via mobile app

## Supabase Client Rules — CRITICAL
- Browser components — lib/supabase/client.ts — respects RLS, has build-time fallbacks
- API routes and server — lib/supabase/server.ts — cookie-based auth, respects RLS
- Admin and cron jobs — lib/supabase/admin.ts — service role key, bypasses RLS
- Middleware — lib/supabase/middleware.ts — auth session refresh
- Never use browser client in API routes — causes auth failures

## Database Rules
- Always use get_my_role() in RLS policies — migrations 017 and above
- Migrations before 017 use current_user_role() — never change old migrations
- Latest migration number is in AGENTS.md — always verify before creating new one
- Always use IF NOT EXISTS on all indexes
- Never drop tables without checking row count first
- Always use soft delete — set is_active = false — never hard delete
- All financial records immutable — never update, only reverse with new record
- Every table needs created_at and updated_at with auto-update trigger
- Always push to abijithcb branch — NEVER push to main

## Pricing and GST Rules
- MRP is always inclusive of 18% GST — never exclusive
- Base price = MRP / 1.18
- GST amount = MRP minus base price
- Discount applied per product line on MRP before GST split
- Discounted MRP = MRP minus discount amount
- Generated columns in subject_accessories: discount_amount, discounted_mrp, base_price, gst_amount, line_total
- Flat discount cannot exceed MRP
- Percentage discount cannot exceed 100
- WAC updates automatically on every stock entry via trigger
- WAC resets to new purchase price when stock quantity was zero
- Selling price can never go below MRP
- All monetary values rounded to 2 decimal places
- Never manually calculate GST — always use MRP / 1.18

## Business Rules
- Technician bag capacity = 50 items max per day per technician
- Attendance toggle ON required before 10:30 AM
- Attendance auto OFF at midnight via cron
- Subject number uniqueness per brand OR per dealer — not global
- AMC chains — new AMC start date must be after previous ends — cannot overlap
- Variance in technician bag deducted from payout automatically
- Payout amount set manually after job completion — cannot pay without amount set
- Subject status flow: pending → allocated → accepted → arrived → in_progress → completed or incomplete
- Status values are always lowercase — never uppercase ever
- In-warranty jobs require 6 photos plus video before completion
- Out-of-warranty jobs require 3 photos before completion
- MRP: latest invoice MRP always auto-updates product MRP

## Error Handling — Always Three Layers
- Repository — catch DB error, throw with context message
- Service — catch repo error, add business context
- Hook — catch service error, show Sonner toast notification
- UI — show error state, never crash, never show raw Supabase errors
- Error response format: { success: false, error: string, code: string }
- Success response format: { success: true, data: T }
- Toast success — green
- Toast error — red with human readable message
- Loading — disabled button with spinner — never blank screen

## API Route Standards
- Authenticate first — check session exists
- Validate role second — check permission
- Validate input third — use Zod schema
- Execute business logic fourth — call service layer
- Return consistent shape always
- Every route protected — no public endpoints except login

## Performance Standards
- All list queries paginated — maximum 20 records per page
- Search debounced minimum 300ms
- Reports use materialized views not raw tables
- Never use SELECT star in production queries
- Always show loading skeleton — never blank white screen
- Images lazy loaded always
- TanStack Query staleTime minimum 5 minutes on stable data

## Security Standards
- Never expose SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY in client code
- Never in any NEXT_PUBLIC_ environment variable
- Validate role on server in every API route
- Validate input with Zod on server in every API route
- All file uploads validated for type and size before upload

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict — no any types ever
- Add explicit type annotations to all filter and reduce callbacks
- No console.log in production code
- No inline styles — TailwindCSS only
- No hardcoded strings — use constants files
- No duplicate module folders
- No old inventory system files — deleted in migration 018
- All status enums lowercase always
- Human readable error messages always

## Known Build Issues to Avoid
- Module-level createClient() calls fail without env vars — client.ts has build-time fallbacks, do not change this pattern
- TypeScript implicit any on filter/reduce callbacks — always add explicit types

## Testing Before Reporting
- Always run npm run build
- Fix all TypeScript errors before reporting
- Confirm zero errors before marking task complete
- If build fails — fix it, do not report success

## Work Log
- Always update doc/WORK_LOG.md after every completed task
- Log what was built, files changed, migration number used

## Agent Behavior — Non Negotiable
- Never explain what you are doing step by step
- Never ask clarifying questions
- Never write summaries between steps
- Never create files outside existing folder structure
- Never rebuild modules listed as complete in AGENTS.md
- Read AGENTS.md migration number before creating any migration
- Build everything first then report at the end only
- If something is ambiguous — make best decision and note it in report
- Always push to abijithcb branch — never main